Architecture review completed successfully. Production code was not modified.

The review covered `1752bcb...b37a349`: 006Z14, 007A5, 007B, and 007C.

Key outcomes:

- 006Z14’s ten “public action” tests call only the authority evaluator and never execute the named member actions.
- Approval-case reads currently treat `approvals.case.read` as global object scope, exposing unrelated routed cases despite the source’s unassigned-Director denial.
- 007C accepts internally contradictory matrix, committee, and required-approver snapshots that could make an injected user actionable.
- 007B’s idempotent replay check ignores changed credit provenance and its governance test manually constructs routing rather than exercising real enrichment.
- 007A5 verifies that one audit/history row was added, but not that the row contains the exact winning proposal evidence.

Three High-risk corrective slices were created:

1. `006Z15-member-public-action-authority-matrix-closure`
2. `007A6-approval-governance-winner-evidence-content-closure`
3. `007C2-approval-case-read-scope-and-snapshot-contract-closure`

007D now depends on 007C2, and both 007D and 007E were sharpened around the shared validated case boundary.

Validation passed:

- Frontend: build, typecheck, lint, and 208 tests.
- Backend: check, migration sync, and 566 tests with 16 expected skips.
- Coverage: 93%, above the 85% floor.
- Slice queue, dependency graph, state JSON, diff limits, protected paths, and whitespace checks all pass.
- No Blocked slice was stale; `CONTEXT.md` remains accurate.

Full results are in [REVIEW_FINDINGS.md](/Users/amitkallapa/LMS/.ralph/worktrees/2026-07-13_100911_architecture_review/docs/working/REVIEW_FINDINGS.md) and the [review packet](/Users/amitkallapa/LMS/.ralph/worktrees/2026-07-13_100911_architecture_review/.ralph/runs/2026-07-13_100911_architecture_review/review-packet.md).

